The paper deals with the problem of optimal scheduling of advertisements in live online social media, which involves decision-making under uncertainty and optimization of revenue. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), social and information networks (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
